agentCompany.name: agentCompany
agentCompany.description: Agent's company name (e.g. Fujitsu Siemens Computers); Not supported.

agentBuild.name: agentBuild
agentBuild.description: Compilation time and date of agent program; Not supported.

agentWriteAllowed.name: agentWriteAllowed
agentWriteAllowed.description: Defines whether writable objects can be written (except shutdown/power-off operations); Not supported.

agentShutdownAllowed.name: agentShutdownAllowed
agentShutdownAllowed.description: Defines whether shutdown/power-off objects can be written; Not supported.

localServerUnitId.name: localServerUnitId
localServerUnitId.description: Unit identifier number of the local server (usually is ID 1). This ID can be used as index into the units table.

numberUnits.name: numberUnits
numberUnits.description: Number of available units (size of units table).

unitTable.name: unitTable
unitTable.description: Description of all units in this MIB

unitCainetNr.name: unitCainetNr
unitCainetNr.description: Physical identification number or partition identification number of units. The ID of the 'chassis' is usually 0.

unitDesignation.name: unitDesignation
unitDesignation.description: Unit identification name. (e.g. 'SB#1') This object returns 'Part Number'; if the index shows chassis.

unitModelName.name: unitModelName
unitModelName.description: Unit model name (e.g. 'PRIMERGY PRIMEQUEST 3200 model xxx')

frontDoorStatus.name: frontDoorStatus
frontDoorStatus.description: Status describing whether the front door is open or closed; Not supported.

housingOpenStatus.name: housingOpenStatus
housingOpenStatus.description: Status describing whether the housing is open or closed; Not supported.

msgLogLanguages.name: msgLogLanguages
msgLogLanguages.description: Supported languages of text message log (comma-seperated list of decimal language codes; see sc2MessageTextLogTable). e.g. '1031;1033' means German and English are supported. English (1033) is the default language and is always available; Not supported.

unitWorldWideName.name: unitWorldWideName
unitWorldWideName.description: Unit World Wide Name. A 64-bit sized address for storage devices (e.g. '6661E2B0A00B88FB'); Not supported.

remcsId.name: remcsId
remcsId.description: REMCS system identification string (binary data); Not supported. Format of Fujitsu REMCS ID (40byte) Format = TTMMMMMMMMMMMMmmmmmmmmmmmmCCnnnnnnnnnnnn TT : 2byte : Type ID for Company Name MM...M : 12byte : Model Name mm...m : 12byte : Device Name CC : 2byte : Checksum nn...n : 12byte : Serial number

unitManagementIpAddress.name: unitManagementIpAddress
unitManagementIpAddress.description: IPv4 address of the partition for management purpose (e.g. '192.168.0.140')

unitManagementIpAddressV6.name: unitManagementIpAddressV6
unitManagementIpAddressV6.description: IPv6 address of the partition for management purpose (e.g. '2001:0db8:0000:85a3:0000:0000:ac1f:8001')

unitTableUpdateCount.name: unitTableUpdateCount
unitTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the unit table. This counter is incremented with every table contents change/update.

parentUnit.name: parentUnit
parentUnit.description: Parent unit. This is the same value as in the object of 'pParentNr'.

parentUnitClass.name: parentUnitClass
parentUnitClass.description: Unit classification (type). This is the same value as in units table.

childUnit.name: childUnit
childUnit.description: Child unit. This is the same value as in the object of 'cChildNr'.

childUnitClass.name: childUnitClass
childUnitClass.description: Unit classification (type). This is the same value as in units table.

parentChildTableUpdateCount.name: parentChildTableUpdateCount
parentChildTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the parent-child unit table. This counter is incremented with every table contents change/update.

managementNodeTable.name: managementNodeTable
managementNodeTable.description: SNMP management node addresses (how to address the units)

unitNodeClass.name: unitNodeClass
unitNodeClass.description: Management node class: primary: operating system interface secondary: remote management controller interface management-blade: management blade in blade server secondary-backup: backup remote management controller interface

unitNodeMacAddress.name: unitNodeMacAddress
unitNodeMacAddress.description: Management node hardware (MAC) address; ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff if value not available

unitNodeUseDHCP.name: unitNodeUseDHCP
unitNodeUseDHCP.description: Management node uses DHCP to obtain its address

unitNodeControllerType.name: unitNodeControllerType
unitNodeControllerType.description: The type of the remote management controller (for identification); like 'RSB'; 'RSB S2'; 'RSB S2 LP'... These names will not be changed if defined once; Not supported.

unitNodeControllerModel.name: unitNodeControllerModel
unitNodeControllerModel.description: The model name of the remote management controller (for displaying); like 'Remote Service Board'; RemoteView Service Board S2'c This name should not be used for identification;only for displaying (can be changed in different firmware versions)! Not supported.

unitNodeControllerFWVersion.name: unitNodeControllerFWVersion
unitNodeControllerFWVersion.description: The FW version of the remote management controller; Not supported.

nodeTableUpdateCount.name: nodeTableUpdateCount
nodeTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the management node table. This counter is incremented with every table contents change/update.

managementChannelType.name: managementChannelType
managementChannelType.description: The type of the management channel currently used (this MIB instance).

spBatteryDischargeTime.name: spBatteryDischargeTime
spBatteryDischargeTime.description: Maximum time (in seconds) this backup battery can discharged. after that a shutdown will be performed (-1 = unknown); Not supported.

spTimeOnBattery.name: spTimeOnBattery
spTimeOnBattery.description: Time (in seconds) the service processor is running on battery since power fail (will be cleared on power recovery); Not supported.

spDoBatteryChargeCycle.name: spDoBatteryChargeCycle
spDoBatteryChargeCycle.description: Perform a discharge/charge cycle on the backup battery by writing a non-zero value. Reading this object just returns the value 0; Not supported.

spBatteryChargeLevel.name: spBatteryChargeLevel
spBatteryChargeLevel.description: Reads the current charge level of the rechargeable battery (in percent of the maximum capacity); Not supported.

managedUpsNodeTable.name: managedUpsNodeTable
managedUpsNodeTable.description: UPS nodes managed by the units; Not supported.

upsIpAddress.name: upsIpAddress
upsIpAddress.description: UPS IP address (represented as string; may also contain an IP V6 address); Not supported.

upsMibRoot.name: upsMibRoot
upsMibRoot.description: UPS MIB root OID; specifies the root OID of the MIB to be used to query UPS via SNMP (empty string if no SNMP agent available); Not supported.

upsSnmpCommunity.name: upsSnmpCommunity
upsSnmpCommunity.description: UPS SNMP community name (empty string if no SNMP agent available); Not supported.

upsHttpPort.name: upsHttpPort
upsHttpPort.description: UPS HTTP interface port; specifies the TCP port number for accessing the UPS management interface via HTTP (0 if no HTTP server available); Not supported.

serverTable.name: serverTable
serverTable.description: Table containing information about the available servers

srvPhysicalMemory.name: srvPhysicalMemory
srvPhysicalMemory.description: Size of physical main memory installed (MBytes); Not supported.

srvLastBootResult.name: srvLastBootResult
srvLastBootResult.description: Result of last system boot; Not supported.

srvCurrentBootStatus.name: srvCurrentBootStatus
srvCurrentBootStatus.description: Status of the current boot unknown(1)' returns; during the Power-on->POST and the shutdown->Power-off.

srvShutdownCommand.name: srvShutdownCommand
srvShutdownCommand.description: Shutdown the server and switch off or reset; a delay (see object below) can be defined before the command is being executed; on reading that value you get the currently pending or executing command value; argument tells what kind of action: power-on: switch power on power-off: switch power off power-cycle: switch power off and switch power on again. shutdown-and-off: execute a shutdown then power off shutdown-and-reset: execute a shutdown then reset shutdown-and-power-cycle: execute a shutdown then power off and on again raise-nmi: raise an NMI (normally causes debugger to start) The value unknown(1) cannot be set; Not supported.

srvShutdownDelay.name: srvShutdownDelay
srvShutdownDelay.description: Delay time (seconds) the agent waits before executing the shutdown command (see previous command). 0 = immediate action; no delay -1 = unknown (delay not supported) The value unknown(-1) cannot be set; Not supported.

srvUUID.name: srvUUID
srvUUID.description: Universal Unique ID (UUID) number - this is a world wide unique ID number of the server. Can be used for identifying a server. The format is like this: 157E465A-A4AC-D711-A847-DD85CECD12EC.

srvPhysicalMemoryOs.name: srvPhysicalMemoryOs
srvPhysicalMemoryOs.description: Size of physical main memory available to the operating system (MBytes). This value is similar to sc2srvPhysicalMemory'; but may be less if the system has mirror or hot spare memory modules; Not supported.

lastPowerOffSource.name: lastPowerOffSource
lastPowerOffSource.description: Reason why the system was switched off last time; Not supported.

lastPowerOnSource.name: lastPowerOnSource
lastPowerOnSource.description: Source the system was switched on from; Not supported.

lastPowerOnTime.name: lastPowerOnTime
lastPowerOnTime.description: Time and Date the system was booted (seconds since 1/1/1970; -1 = unknown); Not supported.

powerOnCounts.name: powerOnCounts
powerOnCounts.description: Tells how often the server was switched on in its life (-1 = unknown); Not supported.

powerOnDuration.name: powerOnDuration
powerOnDuration.description: Tells how long the system has stayed ON in its life (in hours; -1 = unknown); Not supported.

powerOffDuration.name: powerOffDuration
powerOffDuration.description: Tells how long the system has stayed OFF in its life (in hours; -1 = unknown); Not supported.

powerFailRecovery.name: powerFailRecovery
powerFailRecovery.description: Action on AC power recovery after AC has failed. not-available(2) : function not available; behavior is hardware-defined. as-before(3) : server gets the same power state as before the AC fail. remain-off(4) : server remains off on power resume. switch-on(5) : server is always switched on on power resume. schedule-sync(6) : server synchronizes the power state with the schedule setting.

powerCommand.name: powerCommand
powerCommand.description: Switch the unit on or off; argument tells what kind of action: on: switch power on off: switch power off power-cycle: switch power off and switch power on again. The value unknown(1) cannot be set; Not supported.

powerSupplyRedundancy.name: powerSupplyRedundancy
powerSupplyRedundancy.description: Specifies whether the power supply system contains redundant power supplies: 0 : no redundant power supplies available 1 : redundant power supplies available

performanceTable.name: performanceTable
performanceTable.description: Server performance and utilization information; Not supported.

perfType.name: perfType
perfType.description: Server performance object type (description see below); Not supported.

performanceValue.name: performanceValue
performanceValue.description: Server performance value (value interpretation depending on type):; Not supported. cpu: Load of a single CPU in percent cpu-overall: Overall CPU load in percent pci-load: PCI bus load in percent pci-efficiency: PCI bus efficiency in percent (100% is optimum) pci-transfer: PCI bus transfer rate in MBytes/sec. memory-physical: Physical memory usage in MBytes memory-total: Total memory usage (physical + virtual) in MBytes memory-percent: Physical memory usage in percent

performanceName.name: performanceName
performanceName.description: Name (short description) of the performance value (e.g. 'CPU1'). Can be used for displaying a list of performance values in the management frontend; Not supported.

timerOnOffTable.name: timerOnOffTable
timerOnOffTable.description: Power on/off timer table; Not supported.

tooDayOfWeek.name: tooDayOfWeek
tooDayOfWeek.description: Day of the week the times should act upon (index); 1=Sunday 2=Monday... ; Not supported.

onTime.name: onTime
onTime.description: Time the system should be switched on (by the real-time clock; in minutes since midnight; -1 = disabled; no on time). Only values -1 and 0..1439 are allowed; Not supported.

offTime.name: offTime
offTime.description: Time the system should be switched off (by the real-time clock of software; in minutes since midnight; -1 = disabled; no on time). Only values -1 and 0..1439 are allowed; Not supported.

pmCurrentPowerMonitoringAvailable.name: pmCurrentPowerMonitoringAvailable
pmCurrentPowerMonitoringAvailable.description: Power monitoring and control available on this server: true: Power monitoring and power control is available false: Power monitoring and power control is not available

pmCurrentPowerMonitoringEnabled.name: pmCurrentPowerMonitoringEnabled
pmCurrentPowerMonitoringEnabled.description: Power monitoring enable value: true: Power monitoring and data gathering is enabled false: Power monitoring and data gathering is disabled or not available

pmNominalPowerConsumption.name: pmNominalPowerConsumption
pmNominalPowerConsumption.description: Nominal (maximum) value of the system's power consumption (in Watts; -1 if value not available)

pmCurrentPowerConsumption.name: pmCurrentPowerConsumption
pmCurrentPowerConsumption.description: Current value of the system's power consumption (in Watts; 4294967295(0xffffffff) if value not available)

pmCurrentPowerControl.name: pmCurrentPowerControl
pmCurrentPowerControl.description: Power mode control value; Not supported. disabled: The baseboard management controller does not control the power saving behaviour best-performance: The baseboard management controller gives best performance to the system (power consumption may be increased) minimum-power: The baseboard management controller controls the system in way to consume minimum power (performance may be reduced) automatic: The baseboard management controller automatically controls power consumption between good performance and low power consumption scheduled: The baseboard management controller controls power consumption by schedule

pmPowerLimitThreshold.name: pmPowerLimitThreshold
pmPowerLimitThreshold.description: Maximum limit value of the system's power consumption (in Watts; -1 if value not available; only valid if limiting enabled)

pmPowerControlMode.name: pmPowerControlMode
pmPowerControlMode.description: Configured power control mode value: disabled: The management controller does not control the power saving behaviour best-performance: The management controller gives best performance to the system (power consumption may be increased) minimum-power: The management controller controls the system in way to consume minimum power (performance may be reduced) automatic: The management controller automatically controls power consumption between good performance and low power consumption scheduled: The management controller controls power consumption by schedule limited: The management controller controls power consumption by power limit low-noise: The management controller controls the power to ensure running

pmPowerDisplayUnit.name: pmPowerDisplayUnit
pmPowerDisplayUnit.description: Configurd unit for the display of power consumption values: Watt: Power consumption values are displayed in Watts Btu/h: Power consumption values are displyed in Btu

utilizationHistoryTable.name: utilizationHistoryTable
utilizationHistoryTable.description: Utilization history table (for power consumption); table only contains existing values (no values for non-existing values); Not supported.

uthEntity.name: uthEntity
uthEntity.description: Utilization value entity; describes what kind of value to be requested; Not supported. powerConsumptionDay: power consumption values of the last 24 hours; one value (Watts) per minute powerConsumptionMonth: power consumption values of the last month; one value (Watts) per hour powerConsumptionYear: power consumption values of the last year; one value (Watts) per day

uthTimeStamp.name: uthTimeStamp
uthTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of the currenty history entry (time_t = seconds since 1/1/1970; 0:00 AM); Not supported.

uthHardwareUUID.name: uthHardwareUUID
uthHardwareUUID.description: UUID of the hardware instance that delivered the value (from object sc2srvUUID); may change if an installation is migrated to another hardware (e.g. in blade environments); Not supported.

uthAverageValue.name: uthAverageValue
uthAverageValue.description: Average value (in Watts) within the monitored time period (minute; hour; day); Not supported.

uthMinValue.name: uthMinValue
uthMinValue.description: Minimum (lowest) value within the monitored time period; Not supported.

uthMaxValue.name: uthMaxValue
uthMaxValue.description: Maximum (highest) value within the monitored time period; Not supported.

psiPowerSourcePhase.name: psiPowerSourcePhase
psiPowerSourcePhase.description: System input phase of power source.

psiPowerSourceVoltage.name: psiPowerSourceVoltage
psiPowerSourceVoltage.description: System nominal input voltage of power source (in Volts; -1 if value not available).

tempSensorIdentifier.name: tempSensorIdentifier
tempSensorIdentifier.description: Temperature sensor identification string (e.g. TEMP-RSB1); Not supported.

tempSensorStatus.name: tempSensorStatus
tempSensorStatus.description: Status of the temperature sensor Status mapping. SEL level MIB Value Warning temperature-warning(6) Error temperature-critical(7) Error failed(5)

tempCurrentTemperature.name: tempCurrentTemperature
tempCurrentTemperature.description: Current temperature at this sensor (degrees Celsius). This object returns 0; if the agent can not get the value.

tempCriticalLevel.name: tempCriticalLevel
tempCriticalLevel.description: Maximum temperature - critical level (degrees Celsius). system shutdown may occur if this level is exceeded.

tempCriticalReaction.name: tempCriticalReaction
tempCriticalReaction.description: Reaction if temperature exceeds the critical level.

fanIdentifier.name: fanIdentifier
fanIdentifier.description: Fan identification string (e.g. FAN-1-POWERSUPPLY); Not supported.

fanStatus.name: fanStatus
fanStatus.description: Status of the fan Status mapping. SEL level MIB Value Error failed(5)

fanCurrentSpeed.name: fanCurrentSpeed
fanCurrentSpeed.description: Current fan speed (revolutions per minute). This object returns 0; if the agent can not get the value.

fanQuality.name: fanQuality
fanQuality.description: Quality of fan (in percent of nominal speed - measured at full speed); Not supported.

fanFailShutdownDelay.name: fanFailShutdownDelay
fanFailShutdownDelay.description: Delay time (in seconds) when shutdown should commit on fan fail (if shutdown-and-off is configured; 0 = immediately -1 = unknown; cannot be set); Not supported.

afExhaustAirflowVolume.name: afExhaustAirflowVolume
afExhaustAirflowVolume.description: System exhaust airflow volume ('-1' if value not available)

systemBoardProductNumber.name: systemBoardProductNumber
systemBoardProductNumber.description: Product number (may be identical to ModelName)

systemBoardSerialNumber.name: systemBoardSerialNumber
systemBoardSerialNumber.description: Serial number (not available for all boards)

powerSupplyIdentifier.name: powerSupplyIdentifier
powerSupplyIdentifier.description: Power supply identification string (e.g. PS1); Not supported.

powerSupplyStatus.name: powerSupplyStatus
powerSupplyStatus.description: Power supply status Status mapping. SEL level MIB Value Warning ac-fail(5) Warning predictive-fail(9) Error failed(4) Error not-manageable(8)

psPowerSupplyLoad.name: psPowerSupplyLoad
psPowerSupplyLoad.description: Actual power supply output load in Watts (0 = not available); Not supported.

voltageTable.name: voltageTable
voltageTable.description: Voltages - all voltage values are in 1/100th Volts; a value of 330 means 3.30 Volts (0xffffffff = unknown)

voltageStatus.name: voltageStatus
voltageStatus.description: Voltage status Status mapping. SEL level MIB Value Warning low-warning(7) Warning high-warning(8) Error too-low(4) Error too-high(5)

voltageCurrentValue.name: voltageCurrentValue
voltageCurrentValue.description: Voltage current value. This object returns 0; if the agent can not get the value.(1/100V)

voltageCurrentLoad.name: voltageCurrentLoad
voltageCurrentLoad.description: Current output load on this voltage line. in percent of the maximum load (0xffffffff = unknown); Not supported.

cpuStatus.name: cpuStatus
cpuStatus.description: CPU status Status mapping. SEL level MIB Value Warning disabled(4) Warning prefailed-warning(8) Error failed(6)

cpuManufacturer.name: cpuManufacturer
cpuManufacturer.description: CPU manufacturer name (e.g. Intel); Not supported.

cpuNumberLogicals.name: cpuNumberLogicals
cpuNumberLogicals.description: Number of (physically available) logical CPUs within one physical CPU (for hyper-threading and multi-core CPUs). This is the sum of all cores and all logical CPUs of a hyper-threading CPU; Not supported.

cpuCacheL1Size.name: cpuCacheL1Size
cpuCacheL1Size.description: Size of first level cache (in kBytes; -1 if unknown); Not supported.

cpuCacheL2Size.name: cpuCacheL2Size
cpuCacheL2Size.description: Size of second level cache (in kBytes; -1 if unknown); Not supported.

cpuCacheL3Size.name: cpuCacheL3Size
cpuCacheL3Size.description: Size of third level cache (in kBytes; -1 if unknown)

cpuNumberCores.name: cpuNumberCores
cpuNumberCores.description: Number of (physically available) cores within one physical CPU (for multi-core CPUs; platform dependent)

cpuFamily.name: cpuFamily
cpuFamily.description: CPU family code. This enumerated value is specified by the DMTF SMBIOS specification (processor information; type 4); Not supported.

cpuEnabledCores.name: cpuEnabledCores
cpuEnabledCores.description: Number of effectively enabled cores within one physical CPU (for multi-core CPUs; 0 if unknown)

memModuleStatus.name: memModuleStatus
memModuleStatus.description: Memory module status Status mapping. SEL level MIB Value Warning failed-disabled(4) Warning warning(7) Error error(5) Error configuration-error(9)

memModuleBank.name: memModuleBank
memModuleBank.description: Memory module bank number (-1 if unknown); Not supported.

memModuleCapacity.name: memModuleCapacity
memModuleCapacity.description: Memory module size (capacity in MBytes; -1 if unknown)

memModuleStartAddress.name: memModuleStartAddress
memModuleStartAddress.description: Memory module start address (in MBytes; -1 if unknown); Not supported.

memModuleForm.name: memModuleForm
memModuleForm.description: Memory module form (SIMM DIMM ...); Not supported.

memModuleType.name: memModuleType
memModuleType.description: Memory module type (SDRAM DDRAM DDR2 DDR3 ...); Not supported.

memModuleCorrErrors.name: memModuleCorrErrors
memModuleCorrErrors.description: Number of memory module correctable errors (-1 if unknown); Not supported.

memModuleUncorrErrors.name: memModuleUncorrErrors
memModuleUncorrErrors.description: Number of memory module uncorrectable errors (-1 if unknown); Not supported.

memModuleApproved.name: memModuleApproved
memModuleApproved.description: Memory module approved for this machine; Not supported.

memModuleConfiguration.name: memModuleConfiguration
memModuleConfiguration.description: Memory module configuration; Not supported. unknown(1): Module configuration could not be evaluated normal(2): Module is in normal non-redundant configuration or slot is empty disabled(3): Module is disabled (manually through BIOS setup) hotSpare(4): Module is a hot-spare (standby) module; which will be used as a run-time-replacement for failed modules mirror(5): Module is part of a mirror configuration raid(6): Module is part of a RAID configuration notUsable(7): Module is not usable in the actual configuration because of architectural restrictions This object replaces the previous redundancy status values hot-spare and mirror in sc2memModuleStatus.

memModuleFrequency.name: memModuleFrequency
memModuleFrequency.description: Memory module actual front side bus frequency (in MHz; -1 if unknown). This value is based on the BIOS settings; Not supported.

memModuleMaxFrequency.name: memModuleMaxFrequency
memModuleMaxFrequency.description: Memory module maximum front side bus frequency (in MHz; -1 if unknown). This value is based on memory module SPD data; Not supported.

memModuleVoltInterface.name: memModuleVoltInterface
memModuleVoltInterface.description: Memory module interface voltage interface description; Not supported.

cpuMultithreadEnable.name: cpuMultithreadEnable
cpuMultithreadEnable.description: Multithreading of CPU enabled; Not supported.

componentPowerConsumptionTable.name: componentPowerConsumptionTable
componentPowerConsumptionTable.description: Table of component power consumption data; Not supported.

cpcComponentClass.name: cpcComponentClass
cpcComponentClass.description: Component class enumeration (based on IPMI v1.0 entity ID); Not supported.

cpcComponentIndex.name: cpcComponentIndex
cpcComponentIndex.description: Component index within class (1..n); Not supported.

cpcCurrentValue.name: cpcCurrentValue
cpcCurrentValue.description: Current component power consumption in Watts; Not supported.

trustedPlatformModuleTable.name: trustedPlatformModuleTable
trustedPlatformModuleTable.description: Trusted Platform Module (TPM) status information (see corresponding TPM specification for detailed description of these states)

tpmHardwareAvailable.name: tpmHardwareAvailable
tpmHardwareAvailable.description: TPM hardware is available ('unknown' if hardware availability cannot be detected; no interface found)

tpmBiosEnabled.name: tpmBiosEnabled
tpmBiosEnabled.description: TPM hardware is enabled by BIOS ('unknown' if hardware is not available; a reboot is required to change this value)

tpmEnabled.name: tpmEnabled
tpmEnabled.description: TPM is enabled (by software; cannot take ownership if disabled; 'unknown' if hardware is not available or disabled)

tpmActivated.name: tpmActivated
tpmActivated.description: TPM is activated (by software; 'unknown' if hardware is not available or disabled)

tpmOwnership.name: tpmOwnership
tpmOwnership.description: TPM ownership is established (valid endorsement key is existing; 'unknown' if hardware is not available or disabled)

messageLogTable.name: messageLogTable
messageLogTable.description: Error and event message handling; Not supported.

msgLogEntryNr.name: msgLogEntryNr
msgLogEntryNr.description: Message log entry number (index: 0..n); Not supported..

msgLogEntryData.name: msgLogEntryData
msgLogEntryData.description: Message log entry data (binary; one message per table entry); Not supported..

recoverySettingTable.name: recoverySettingTable
recoverySettingTable.description: ASR&R (Automatic server recovery and restart) settings; Not supported.

asrNrRebootRetries.name: asrNrRebootRetries
asrNrRebootRetries.description: Current number of retries to reboot/restart the server when a failure shutdown (and power-off) had occurred. After this number of retries the action defined in 'sc2asrRebootFailAction' will be executed (-1 = unknown; no retries). The value unknown(1) cannot be set; a SET will deliver 'badValue'; Not supported.

asrDefaultRebootRetries.name: asrDefaultRebootRetries
asrDefaultRebootRetries.description: Default number of retries for server failure reboot. The previous object sc2asrNrRebootRetries will be set to this value after the server is working properly for a certain amount of time; Not supported.

asrNextBootSource.name: asrNextBootSource
asrNextBootSource.description: Source medium to boot from (next time): operating-system: boot from floppy or hard disk diag-system: boot from alternate diagnostic system (only for SCSI systems; load diagnostic system from alternate IDE disk). remote-disk: boot from remote network disk The value unknown(1) cannot be set; a SET will deliver 'badValue'; Not supported.

asrRebootFailAction.name: asrRebootFailAction
asrRebootFailAction.description: Specifies the action after a specified number of failed reboot retries (the object 'sc2asrNrRebootRetries' has reached zero).The value no-diag-system(4) means that a diagnostic system is not available; no other value can be set. The values unknown(1) and reserved(3) cannot be set; a SET will deliver 'badValue'; Not supported.

asrRestartDelay.name: asrRestartDelay
asrRestartDelay.description: Delay (in minutes) when the system should be automatically switched on again (by real-time clock) after an error power-off. Setting this value to zero means immediate restart (power-cycle only). You can disable automatic restart by setting the 'sc2asrRebootFailAction' to 'switch-off' and the 'sc2asrDefaultRebootRetries' to zero; Not supported.

asrPostErrorHalt.name: asrPostErrorHalt
asrPostErrorHalt.description: Describes what to do when a POST error has occurred (halt on any error; no halt on any error...). The values unknown(1) and other(9) cannot be set; a SET will deliver 'badValue'; Not supported.

messageTextLogTable.name: messageTextLogTable
messageTextLogTable.description: Error and event message handling; reported as text strings; Not supported.

msgTextLogLanguage.name: msgTextLogLanguage
msgTextLogLanguage.description: Message log entry language (index; Windows language code); Not supported. e.g. 1031; 1033 for German; English (default; always available)

msgTextLogSeqNr.name: msgTextLogSeqNr
msgTextLogSeqNr.description: Message log entry sequence number (index; 0..n); Not supported.

msgTextLogTimestamp.name: msgTextLogTimestamp
msgTextLogTimestamp.description: Message log entry time stamp (time_t = seconds since 1/1/1970; 0:00 AM); Not supported.

msgTextLogMessage.name: msgTextLogMessage
msgTextLogMessage.description: Message log entry message string (multi-byte string; multi-language; not every language may be implemented); Not supported.

msgTextLogErrorCode.name: msgTextLogErrorCode
msgTextLogErrorCode.description: Message log entry error code; Not supported.

msgTextLogSeverity.name: msgTextLogSeverity
msgTextLogSeverity.description: Message log entry severity; Not supported.

msgTextLogCSSComponent.name: msgTextLogCSSComponent
msgTextLogCSSComponent.description: Component which caused the log message may be replaced by the customer (CSS=Customer Self Service); Not supported.

messageLogActionHintTable.name: messageLogActionHintTable
messageLogActionHintTable.description: Action text strings for error and event messages; Not supported.

mlaLanguage.name: mlaLanguage
mlaLanguage.description: Action text language (index; Windows language code) e.g. 1031; 1033 for German; English; Not supported.

mlaErrorCode.name: mlaErrorCode
mlaErrorCode.description: Action text error code (index); Not supported.

mlaType.name: mlaType
mlaType.description: Message log entry severity; Not supported.

mlaIndex.name: mlaIndex
mlaIndex.description: Action text entry string index (index; 1..n); Not supported.

agentStatus.name: agentStatus
agentStatus.description: Overall status of all monitored components in this agent ok(1): all subsystems and components working properly; no failure degraded(2): at least one component has a problem; system may still work properly error(3): severe problem; system will not work properly failed(4): one or more managed components have failed unknown(5): none of the subsystems had a valid status (e.g. during initialization)

statusComponentTable.name: statusComponentTable
statusComponentTable.description: Table with status values of the components in this agent. The table summarizes all instances of one component to one status value.

componentStatusValue.name: componentStatusValue
